The paper discusses the impact of mmWave communications on TCP performance, which is a topic related to network infrastructure (cs.NI). The paper proposes a novel TCP design for mmWave communications, which involves managing acknowledgments and retransmissions, indicating a focus on information theory (cs.IT) and communication systems (cs.COMM). The paper also discusses the properties of mmWave channels, which could fall under the category of computer architecture (cs.AR) or multimedia (cs.MM).
